1) run display
  open -> grab button

      grab the pattern:

           M ",/^_[`jpqy| M

           /  !"#$%&'()*+ /
           < ,-./01234567 <
           > 89:;<=>?@ABC >
           @ DEFGHIJKLMNO @
           _ PQRSTUVWXYZ[ _
           { \]^_`abcdefg {
           } hijklmnopqrs }
           ~ tuvwxyz{|}~  ~

           M ",/^_[`jpqy| M

	save as grab.pbm

2) pnmcut grab.pbm | pnmcrop > font.pbm

3) pbmtext -font font.pbm 'some text string' > output.pbm

=-=

One can also use builtin fonts:

	pbmtext -builtin fixed 'some text string' > output.pbm

To output in reverse videio:

	pbmtext -builtin fixed 'some text string' | pnminvert > output.pbm

For the fixed font, chars are boxed by a 7 wide x 12 tall pixel grid

The shell script b64.chopup.sh, forms a directory with a 7x12 grid
of 1's and 0's.
